data.name: _btnInsert.ToolTip
data.value:
If Behavior: Insert Behavior from text: 1. Action, CallAction, Activity (loop) 2. Decision 3. Retrun value (return E_L2C_OSQ_OK;)
Decision: - Select Decision - Copy 1 Branch at a time -- First branch with switch (...) statement -- Second... branch without switch (...) statement -- Multiple cases are give a comma separated [GUARD] - Move the created GUARD with actions to the left to make room of the next generation
Issues: - Macros with multiple lines - If with multiple lines - Brackets in decisions
If structural Element: Insert & update attributes from C-Code for selected element:

data.name: _btnSplitNodes.ToolTip
data.value:
Split / disconnect the selected nodes from the last selected element.
- Select some nodes you want to disconnect (sources) - Select the node you want to disconnect from the source nodes (target) - Click S (split disconnect node from previous selected) - hoReverse deletes th flows from sources to the target (last selected element)

data.name: _btnWriteText.ToolTip
data.value:
Writet text in selected Element / Connector
If connector and (ControlFlow or Trigger) write Guard. If connector and not (ControlFlow or Trigger) write Name.
You may read/copy the Text with RT.

data.name: _btnAddNoteAndLink.ToolTip
data.value:
Add Note element and show feature 'Note' of selected nodes/element: - Diagram - Element - Connector - Attribute - Operation
Always remember: - Diagrams are for the reader - The Element/Diagram description is a good place for specifications.

data.name: _btnCopy.ToolTip
data.value:
Copy/Read Text name of selected diagram items or the context item:
- Attribute - Connector Guard or Name - Element(s) - Operation - Package(s)
If the diagram items selected (Elements, Packages) the hoReverse sorts them alphabetic.

data.name: _insertAttributeToolStripMenuItem.ToolTipText
data.value:
Insert & update attributes from C-Code for selected element: - Class/Interface: Attribute (macros) - Enumearation: Eenum values
If attribute/stereotype is different a hoReverse detects a new atttribute.
Macros are defined as: - readonly - stereotype 'define' - Use additional stereotypes - Add '#' at end of stereotype to say not the value
hoReverse handles: #if ( name = stereotype) # define ..... #else # define ..... # define ..... #endif

data.name: _insertTypedefStructToolStripMenuItem.ToolTipText
data.value:
Generates a typedef - struct - union - enum from code.
Select a class/interface to generate the typedef beneath. Select the typedef if you want to update it without changing the parent. hoReverse deletes all old values.

data.name: _generateComponentPortsToolStripMenuItem.ToolTipText
data.value:
Generate ports for selected component: - Interfaces/Classes of diagram give ProvidedInterfaces - Implementation of diagram Classes/Interfaces gives RequiredInterfaces -Extension '*_i': private Interface, no ProvidedInterface
Note: - You have to specify the Implementation file in Propertie (fileName) - FileName, Extension and Modelelement have to consistent

data.name: _inserToolStripMenuItem.ToolTipText
data.value:
Select Class/Interface and generate Interfaces from code.
hoReverse adds theInterfaces with: - 'Usage' dependency if inlude has a different name as the selected Class - 'Realisation' dependency if inlude has the name of the selected

data.name: _setMacroToolStripMenuItem.ToolTipText
data.value:
Set the macro/stereotype according to the comma seperated text list.
Textlist: - Delete all blanks, '(', ')' - If empty use macro "define"
Examples: define, a = b add '<<define>>,<< a=b>>' empty add '<<define>>'

data.name: _addMacroToolStripMenuItem.ToolTipText
data.value:
Add macros/stereotypes according to the comma seperated text list.
Textlist: - Delete all blanks and '(', ')' - If empty add <<define>>
Examples: define, a = b add '<<define>>,<< a=b>>' empty add '<<define>>'

data.name: settingsDiagramStylesToolStripMenuItem.ToolTipText
data.value:
Change settings 'Bulk change Diagram Style': - Opens the Settings.json file to edit it - c:\users\<user>\AppData\Roaming\ho\hoTools\Setting.json
Function: - Package, Element, Diagrams - Package recursive - Templates in Settings.json
One Click, and you have the Diagram Styles according to your selection changed.

data.name: _createActivityForOperationToolStripMenuItem.ToolTipText
data.value:
Create/Update Activity for Method according to selected context:
Select: - Method/Operation - Class/Interface - Package - Activity (only update Activity parameter)
It creates: - Package with name of Method - Activity with name of Method - Activity Parameter - Link Method to Behavior (Activity) - Activity Diagram with name of Method (Activity, ...)
It updates Activities: - Name, Stereotype - Parameter and type
Because the Activity is possible visualized in more than one diagram you have to take care of the different diagrams.

data.name: moveUsageToElementToolStripMenuItem.ToolTipText
data.value:
Move all usages from source to target element - Source: Fist selected Element in Diagram - Target: Second selected Element in Diagram
It updates: - Links - Attribute type - Operation type - Operation Parameter type - Apperance in Diagrams - Appearance in t_xref (conveyed items) - Generalization - Connector updates source and target - Parent of object - Type of object

data.name: showExternalComponentFunctionsToolStripMenuItem.ToolTipText
data.value:
Show the provided and required functions for each EA Component.
Select Component or Class.
The function requires an implementation to work (*.c or *.cpp) and: - Source Code folder with the name of the selected Element OR - Source File with the name of the selected Element and the extension *.c or *.cpp

data.name: showProvidedRequiredFunctionsForSourceToolStripMenuItem.ToolTipText
data.value:
Show the provided and required functions for choosen: - Folder with C-Implementation - *.c/*.cpp file
hoReverse analyzis the choosen folder or source file for: - Required - Provided Interface

data.name: _changeXmlPathToolStripMenuItem1.ToolTipText
data.value: Set/Change the *.xml file path for a VC (Version Controlled) package 1. Check-In the package 2. Checkout the parent package 3. Move the *.xml file to the new location and check it in 4. Click on Set/Change VC *.xml file 5. Enter new *.xml file path 6. Check-in the parent Package
